Prove the following generalized Pascal Identity for \(n,k_1,k_2,k_3\ge 1\)

\[\binom{n}{k_1,k_2,k_3}=\binom{n-1}{k_1-1,k_2,k_3}+\binom{n-1}{k_1,k_2-1,k_3}+\binom{n-1}{k_1,k_2,k_3-1}\]



Proof

\[\binom{n}{k_1,k_2,k_3}=\frac{(n-1)!(k_1+k_2+k_3)}{k_1!k_2!k_3!}\]
\[=\binom{n-1}{k_1-1,k_2,k_3}+\binom{n-1}{k_1,k_2-1,k_3}+\binom{n-1}{k_1,k_2,k_3-1}\]
